(16, 'Mayonnaise And Prepared Sauce Market in the USA - Key Insights', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Mayonnaise And Prepared Sauce Market in the USA - Key Insights\" alt=\"Mayonnaise And Prepared Sauce Market in the USA - Key Insights\" height=\"420\" width=\"722\" src=\"https://www.indexbox.io/published/publicdata/U983154/attachments/SC/products_covers_overlays/311941.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><p>IndexBox has just published a new report, <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/us-mayonnaise-dressing-and-other-prepared-sauces-market-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\">the U.S. Mayonnaise, Dressing, And Other Prepared Sauces Market. Analysis And Forecast to 2025</a>. Here is a summary of the report\'s key findings.</p><p></p><p>The revenue of the mayonnaise and prepared sauce market in the U.S. amounted to $9.4B in 2018, therefore, remained relatively stable against the previous year. This figure reflects the total revenues of producers and importers (excluding logistics costs, retail marketing costs, and retailers\' margins, which will be included in the final consumer price). In general, mayonnaise and prepared sauce consumption continues to indicate a slight downturn. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2016, when it surged by 2.7% y-o-y. Over the period under review, the mayonnaise and prepared sauce market attained its maximum level at $10B in 2014; however, from 2015 to 2018, consumption stood at a somewhat lower figure. </p><b>Production of Mayonnaise, Dressing, And Other Prepared Sauces in the USA</b><br /><br /><p>In value terms, mayonnaise and prepared sauce production stood at $9.1B in 2018. Overall, mayonnaise and prepared sauce production continues to indicate a mild slump. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2016, when it surged by 2.9% against the previous year. </p><b>Production By Type in the USA</b><br /><br /><p>In value terms, the most produced types of mayonnaise, dressing, and other prepared sauces in the U.S. were mayonnaise, salad dressings, and sandwich spreads ($4.6B), prepared sauces (mustard, worcestershire, soy, horseradish, and sauces used as a condiment to meat, vegetable, and seafood), excluding tomato-based sauces and sauces comprised of 20% or more meat ($3.4B) and vinegar and cider ($852M), together comprising 97% of total production. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In terms of the main produced products, vinegar and cider (+11.7% per year) experienced the highest growth rate of mayonnaise and prepared sauce production, over the last five year period, while the other products experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Exports of Mayonnaise, Dressing, And Other Prepared Sauces</b><br /><br /><b>Exports from the USA</b><br /><br /><p>In 2018, the amount of mayonnaise, dressing, and other prepared sauces exported from the U.S. amounted to 154K tonnes, reducing by -23.6% against the previous year. The total export volume increased at an average annual rate of +2.2% over the period from 2013 to 2018; however, the trend pattern indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded in certain years. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2016, when it surged by 14% year-to-year. Over the period under review, mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports reached their peak figure at 202K tonnes in 2017, and then declined slightly in the following year. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports stood at $242M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=n311941&region=0\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2018. The total export value increased at an average annual rate of +4.2% over the period from 2013 to 2018; however, the trend pattern indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded in certain years. Over the period under review, mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports reached their peak figure at $272M in 2017, and then declined slightly in the following year. </p><b>Exports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>Chile (30K tonnes) was the main destination for mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports from the U.S., accounting for a 22% share of total exports. Moreover, mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports to Chile exceeded the volume sent to the second major destination, Sierra Leone (10K tonnes), threefold. Nigeria (8.5K tonnes) ranked third in terms of total exports with a 6.2% share.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the average annual rate of growth in terms of volume to Chile amounted to +31.3%. Exports to the other major destinations recorded the following average annual rates of exports growth: Sierra Leone (+30.1% per year) and Nigeria (+0.4% per year).</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, Chile ($33M) remains the key foreign market for mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports from the U.S., comprising 14% of total mayonnaise and prepared sauce exports. The second position in the ranking was occupied by Sierra Leone ($16M), with a 6.7% share of total exports. It was followed by the United Arab Emirates, with a 6.3% share.</p><b>Export Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The average mayonnaise and prepared sauce export price stood at $1.8 per kg in 2018, rising by 30% against the previous year. Over the last five years, it increased at an average annual rate of +4.4%. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2018, an increase of 30% year-to-year. In that year, the average export prices for mayonnaise, dressing, and other prepared sauces attained their peak level, and is likely to continue its growth in the immediate term. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Export prices varied noticeably by the country of origin; the country with the highest export price was the United Arab Emirates ($1.9 per kg), while the average price for exports to Chile ($1.1 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the most notable rate of growth in terms of export prices was recorded for supplies to Nigeria (+6.1% per year), while the export prices for the other major destinations experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Imports of Mayonnaise, Dressing, And Other Prepared Sauces</b><br /><br /><b>Imports into the USA</b><br /><br /><p>In 2018, approx. 346K tonnes of mayonnaise, dressing, and other prepared sauces were imported into the U.S.; rising by 6.7% against the previous year. The total import volume increased at an average annual rate of +4.0% over the period from 2013 to 2018; the trend pattern remained consistent, with somewhat noticeable fluctuations over the period under review. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, mayonnaise and prepared sauce imports totaled $537M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=n311941&region=0\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2018. The total import value increased at an average annual rate of +5.2% from 2013 to 2018; the trend pattern remained consistent, with only minor fluctuations over the period under review. In that year, mayonnaise and prepared sauce imports attained their peak , and are likely to continue its growth in the immediate term. </p><b>Imports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>China (70K tonnes), Italy (70K tonnes) and Thailand (55K tonnes) were the main suppliers of mayonnaise and prepared sauce imports to the U.S., with a combined 56% share of total imports. China, Hong Kong SAR, Japan, South Korea, the Philippines, France, Taiwan, Chinese and Spain lagged somewhat behind, together comprising a further 30%.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the most notable rate of growth in terms of imports, amongst the main suppliers, was attained by China, Hong Kong SAR (+9.5% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, Italy ($139M), China ($71M) and Thailand ($63M) appeared to be the largest mayonnaise and prepared sauce suppliers to the U.S., with a combined 51% share of total imports. These countries were followed by Japan, China, Hong Kong SAR, South Korea, France, the Philippines, Taiwan, Chinese and Spain, which together accounted for a further 34%.</p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>In 2018, the average mayonnaise and prepared sauce import price amounted to $1.6 per kg, going up by 3.6% against the previous year. Over the period from 2013 to 2018, it increased at an average annual rate of +1.2%. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There were significant differences in the average import prices amongst the major supplying countries. In 2018, the country with the highest import price was Japan ($2.5 per kg), while the price for China ($1 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Japan (+12.3% per year), while the import prices for the other major suppliers experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Companies Mentioned in the Report</b><br /><br /><p>Reckitt Benckiser, T.marzetti Company, Treehouse Foods, Kikkoman Foods, Victoria Fine Foods, Clements Foods, Litehouse, Cains Foods, Lancaster Colony Corporation, McIlhenny Company, Chelten House Products, Spring Silver Foods, Naturally Fresh, Campbell Stockpot Soup, Gff, Bay Valley Foods, Mrs. Stratton\'s Salads, Arcobasso Foods, Hampton Creek, Pacific Choice Brands, Olds Products Co. of Illinois, F S S, Pepper Source, Peppers Unlimited of Louisiana, Unilever United States, Huntsinger Farms, The H V Food Products Company, Conopco, E Mc Ilhenny\'s Son Corporation, The French\'s Food Company, RB Manufacturing</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/us-mayonnaise-dressing-and-other-prepared-sauces-market-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 64, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 0),
(17, 'Strawberry Market in Asia - Key Insights', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Strawberry Market in Asia - Key Insights\" alt=\"Strawberry Market in Asia - Key Insights\" height=\"420\" width=\"722\" src=\"https://www.indexbox.io/published/publicdata/U983154/attachments/SC/products_covers_overlays/Strawberries.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><p>IndexBox has just published a new report, <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/asia-strawberries-market-report-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\">the Asia - Strawberries - Market Analysis, Forecast, Size, Trends and Insights</a>. Here is a summary of the report\'s key findings.</p><p></p><p>The revenue of the strawberry market in Asia amounted to $11.2B in 2017, dropping by -15% against the previous year. This figure reflects the total revenues of producers and importers (excluding logistics costs, retail marketing costs, and retailers\' margins, which will be included in the final consumer price). The strawberry consumption continues to indicate a strong expansion. The most prominent rate of growth was recorded in 2013, with an increase of 34% against the previous year. The level of strawberry consumption peaked at $13.1B in 2016, and then declined slightly in the following year. </p><b>Strawberry Production in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>In value terms, strawberry production stood at $11.7B in 2017 estimated in export prices. The strawberry production continues to indicate a remarkable increase. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2014, when it surged by 36% against the previous year. The level of strawberry production peaked at $13.7B in 2016, and then declined slightly in the following year. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">China (3.7M tonnes) remains the largest strawberry producing country in Asia, accounting for 81% of total production. Moreover, strawberry production in China exceeded the figures recorded by the world\'s second largest producer, Turkey (400K tonnes), ninefold. The third position in this ranking was occupied by South Korea (210K tonnes), with a 4.6% share.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the average annual rate of growth in terms of volume in China stood at +7.1%. In the other countries, the average annual rates were as follows: Turkey (+4.8% per year) and South Korea (+0.3% per year).</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In 2017, average strawberry yield in Asia stood at 27 tonne per ha, growing by 2.8% against the previous year. The  yield figure increased at an average annual rate of +1.6% over the period from 2007 to 2017; the trend pattern remained consistent, with only minor fluctuations being recorded over the period under review. The most prominent rate of growth was recorded in 2012, with an increase of 5.9% year-to-year. The level of strawberry yield peaked in 2017, and is expected to retain its growth in the immediate term. Despite the increased use of modern agricultural techniques and methods, future yield figures may still be impacted by adverse weather conditions.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The strawberry harvested area stood at 169K ha in 2017, coming down by -3.9% against the previous year. The total harvested area indicated a strong growth from 2007 to 2017: its figure increased at an average annual rate of +4.2% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. Based on 2017 figures, the strawberry harvested area increased by +52.8% against 2008 indices. The most prominent rate of growth was recorded in 2015, when the harvested area increased by 10% y-o-y. </p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Strawberry Exports</b><br /><br /><b>Exports in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>The exports stood at 25K tonnes in 2017, going up by 15% against the previous year. The strawberry exports continue to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, strawberry exports amounted to $87M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=081010&region=966\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. The total exports indicated a strong increase from 2007 to 2017: its value increased at an average annual rate of +0.4% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. Based on 2017 figures, the strawberry exports increased by +61.9% against 2011 indices. Over the period under review, strawberry exports attained their maximum in 2017, and are expected to retain its growth in the near future. </p><b>Exports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>Turkey was the main exporter of strawberries in Asia, with the volume of exports finishing at 9.1K tonnes, which was approx. 36% of total exports in 2017. South Korea (4.8K tonnes) occupied a 19% share (based on tonnes) of total exports, which put it in second place, followed by Japan (15%), China (9.1%), Jordan (8.5%) and Syrian Arab Republic (7.8%). </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of exports, amongst the main exporting countries, was attained by South Korea (+26.6% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, South Korea ($43M) remains the largest strawberry supplier in Asia, comprising 49% of global exports. The second position in the ranking was occupied by Turkey ($12M), with a 14% share of global exports. It was followed by Japan, with a 12% share.</p><b>Export Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The strawberry export price in Asia stood at $3.5 per kg in 2017, rising by 3.8% against the previous year. The the strawberry export price continues to indicate a prominent growth. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There were significant differences in the average export prices amongst the major exporting countries. In 2017, the country with the highest export price was South Korea ($9 per kg), while Turkey ($1.4 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of export prices was attained by China (+6.8% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Strawberry Imports</b><br /><br /><b>Imports in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, the amount of strawberries imported in Asia stood at 72K tonnes, increasing by 12% against the previous year. The strawberry imports continue to indicate a remarkable increase. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, strawberry imports stood at $289M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=081010&region=966\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. The strawberry imports continue to indicate a remarkable growth. The level of imports peaked in 2017, and are expected to retain its growth in the immediate term. </p><b>Imports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, Saudi Arabia (18K tonnes), the United Arab Emirates (12K tonnes), China, Hong Kong SAR (10K tonnes), Singapore (8K tonnes) and Japan (7.9K tonnes) represented the largest importers of strawberries in Asia, committing 78% of total import. It was distantly followed by Kuwait (4K tonnes), constituting 5.6% share of total imports. Thailand (2.2K tonnes) held the minor share of total imports. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of imports, amongst the main importing countries, was attained by Thailand (+20.9% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, China, Hong Kong SAR ($62M), Saudi Arabia ($54M) and the United Arab Emirates ($46M) constituted the countries with the highest levels of imports in 2017, together comprising 56% of total imports. Japan, Singapore, Kuwait and Thailand lagged somewhat behind, together accounting for a further 31%.</p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The strawberry import price in Asia stood at $4 per kg in 2017, coming down by -2.1% against the previous year. Over the period from 2007 to 2017, it increased at an average annual rate of +3.1%. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Import prices varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest import price was China, Hong Kong SAR ($6.2 per kg), while Saudi Arabia ($3.1 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Saudi Arabia (+10.4% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/asia-strawberries-market-report-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 11, '2019-07-19 22:44:15', 0),
