rice amounted to $4.1 per kg, going up by 2.9% against the previous year. Overall, the plastic plumbing fixture import price continues to indicate a slight decline. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Import prices varied noticeably by the country of origin; the country with the highest import price was Germany ($6.4 per kg), while the price for China ($3.7 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Egypt (+1.7% per year), while the import prices for the other major suppliers experienced mixed trend patterns.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Companies Mentioned in the Report</b><br /><br /><p>Best Bath Systems, Jacuzzi Inc., MTI Baths, R. W. Lyall & Company, Aquatic Co., The Praxis Companies LLC, Danze, The Onyx Collection, Le Elegant Bath, Strong Industries, Lyons Industries, Duo-Form Acquisition Corp., Fiber Care Baths, Mdm Enterprises, Peggy S. Lane, Spurlin Industries, Bathcraft, Clarke Products, Kinro Composites, L & M Laminates and Marble, Frontline Mfg., Cincinnati Machines, Jacuzzi Whirlpool Bath, Maax Spas Industries Corp., Hansgroag, Gatsby Spas, Lasco Composites, Aquatic Industries, The Lozier Foundation, Maax US Corp., Toto U.S.A. Holdings</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/us-plastic-plumbing-fixture-market-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 114, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 0),
