 ($131M), with a 13% share of total imports. It was followed by Taiwan, Chinese, with a 6.8% share.</p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The average blind and shade import price stood at $3.3 per kg in 2018, surging by 5.8% against the previous year. In general, the blind and shade import price continues to indicate a mild increase. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There were significant differences in the average import prices amongst the major supplying countries. In 2018, the country with the highest import price was Taiwan, Chinese ($5.8 per kg), while the price for Viet Nam ($1.8 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Cambodia (+11.4% per year), while the import prices for the other major suppliers experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Companies Mentioned in the Report</b><br /><br /><p>Hunter Douglas, Mechoshade Systems, The Kittrich Corporation, Kenney Manufacturing Company, 3 Day Blinds, Springs Window Fashions, Comfortex Corporation, Qmotion Incorporated, Aerospace Technologies Group, Timber Blinds Mfg., Lafayette Venetian Blind, Vista Products, Skagfield Corporation, Selective Enterprises, MGM Industries, Century Blinds, Mechoshade West, Blinds To Go (u.s.) Inc., Vertical Retail Solutions, American Drapery Blind & Carpet, Legacy Window Coverings, Hd Window Fashions, Hunter Douglas Window Fashions, Hunter Douglas Fabrications, Superior Shade and Blind Co., Hunter Douglas Fabrication Co, Springs Industries, Custom Brands Group, Newell Window Furnishings, Ggc Administration, Turnils North America, 3form</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/us-blinds-and-shades-market-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 77, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 0),
(64, 'Methanol Market in Asia - Key Insights', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><p>IndexBox has just published a new report, <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/asia-methanol-methyl-alcohol-market-analysis-forecast-size-trends-and-insights/\">the Asia - Methanol (Methyl Alcohol) - Market Analysis, Forecast, Size, Trends And Insights</a>. Here is a summary of the report\'s key findings.</p><p></p><p>The revenue of the methanol market in Asia amounted to $8.7B in 2017, surging by 52% against the previous year. This figure reflects the total revenues of producers and importers (excluding logistics costs, retail marketing costs, and retailers\' margins, which will be included in the final consumer price). The total market indicated a strong increase from 2007 to 2017: its value increased at an average annual rate of +3.4% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. The most prominent rate of growth was recorded in 2017, with an increase of 52% y-o-y. The level of methanol consumption peaked at $8.8B in 2014; however, from 2015 to 2017, consumption remained at a lower figure. </p><b>Production in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>The methanol production stood at 21M tonnes in 2017, increasing by 3.2% against the previous year. The methanol production continues to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2008, with an increase of 19% y-o-y. In that year, methanol production reached its peak volume of 27M tonnes. From 2009 to 2017, methanol production growth remained at a lower figure. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p></p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Methanol Exports</b><br /><br /><b>Exports in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>The exports amounted to 13M tonnes in 2017, coming down by -8.4% against the previous year. The methanol exports continue to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, methanol exports amounted to $4.4B (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=290511&region=966\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. The total exports indicated a strong increase from 2007 to 2017: its value decreased at an average annual rate of -0.3% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. The level of exports peaked at $4.9B in 2012; however, from 2013 to 2017, exports failed to regain their momentum. </p><b>Exports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>Iran (4M tonnes) and Saudi Arabia (3.7M tonnes) represented the main exporters of methanol (methyl alcohol) in 2017, amounting to near 32% and 30% of total exports, respectively. It was distantly followed by Malaysia (1.8M tonnes), Oman (1.2M tonnes) and Qatar (698K tonnes), together committing 29% share of total exports. Brunei Darussalam (492K tonnes) and Bahrain (312K tonnes) followed a long way behind the leaders. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of exports, amongst the main exporting countries, was attained by Malaysia (+14.8% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, Iran ($1.3B), Saudi Arabia ($1.3B) and Oman ($681M) constituted the countries with the highest levels of exports in 2017, with a combined 74% share of total exports. </p><b>Export Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The methanol export price in Asia stood at $351 per tonne in 2017, increasing by 61% against the previous year. The the methanol export price continues to indicate a prominent expansion. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Export prices varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest export price was Oman ($573 per tonne), while Brunei Darussalam ($283 per tonne) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the mos