nes), South Korea (7.8K tonnes), Thailand (6.8K tonnes) and Turkey (5.8K tonnes) held the mild share of total imports. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of imports, amongst the main importing countries, was attained by Saudi Arabia (+22.7% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, Japan ($460M), Saudi Arabia ($446M) and Iraq ($188M) appeared to be the countries with the highest levels of imports in 2017, together accounting for 45% of total imports. The United Arab Emirates, China, India, South Korea, Malaysia, Israel, Kuwait, Turkey and Thailand lagged somewhat behind, together accounting for a further 31%.</p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The carpet import price in Asia stood at $7 per kg in 2017, falling by -15.2% against the previous year. The the carpet import price continues to indicate a measured decline. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2010, when the import price increased by 15% year-to-year. The level of import price peaked at $10 per kg in 2013; however, from 2014 to 2017, import prices stood at a somewhat lower figure. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Import prices varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest import price was South Korea ($11 per kg), while Iraq ($3.7 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Malaysia (+7.2% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/asia-carpets-and-other-textile-floor-coverings-market-analysis-forecast-size-trends-and-insights/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 78, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 0),
(71, 'Steel Wire Market in the USA - Key Insights', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Steel Wire Market in the USA - Key Insights\" alt=\"Steel Wire Market in the USA - Key Insights\" height=\"420\" width=\"722\" src=\"https://www.indexbox.io/published/publicdata/U983154/attachments/SC/products_covers_overlays/331222.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><p>IndexBox has just published a new report, <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/us-steel-wire-market-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\">the U.S. Steel Wire Market. Analysis And Forecast to 2025</a>. Here is a summary of the report\'s key findings.</p><p></p><p>The revenue of the steel wire market in the U.S. amounted to $3.2B in 2018, surging by 14% against the previous year. This figure reflects the total revenues of producers and importers (excluding logistics costs, retail marketing costs, and retailers\' margins, which will be included in the final consumer price). The market value increased at an average annual rate of +1.8% over the period from 2013 to 2018; the trend pattern remained relatively stable, with somewhat noticeable fluctuations being observed in certain years. The pace of growth appeared the most rapid in 2018, when it surged by 14% year-to-year. In that year, the steel wire market reached its peak level, and is likely to continue its growth in the immediate term. </p><b>Steel Wire Production in the USA</b><br /><br /><p>In value terms, steel wire production stood at $5.4B in 2018. Overall, steel wire production continues to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. The most prominent rate of growth was recorded in 2015, with an increase of 2.3% against the previous year. In that year, steel wire production attained its peak level of $5.6B. From 2016 to 2018, steel wire production growth failed to regain its momentum. </p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Steel Wire Exports</b><br /><br /><b>Exports from the USA</b><br /><br /><p>In 2018, the amount of steel wire exported from the U.S. totaled 1.5K tonnes, shrinking by -10.5% against the previous year. Overall, steel wire exports continue to indicate an abrupt reduction. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2014, with an increase of -4.9% y-o-y. Over the period under review, steel wire exports attained their peak figure at 2.6K tonnes in 2013; however, from 2014 to 2018, exports failed to regain their momentum. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, steel wire exports stood at $7M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=n331222&region=0\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2018. Overall, steel wire exports continue to indicate an abrupt decline. In that year, steel wire exports reached their peak  of $15M. From 2015 to 2018, the growth of steel wire exports failed to regain its momentum. </p><b>Exports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The UK (205 tonnes), the Netherlands (138 tonnes) and the Dominican Republic (116 tonnes) were the main destinations of steel wire exports from the U.S., with a combined 30% share of total exports. These countries were followed by New Zealand, South Korea, Australia, Colombia, Honduras, Panama, Guatemala, El Salvador and Antigua and Barbuda, which together accounted for a further 35%.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2013 to 2018, the most notable rate of growth in terms of exports, amongst the main countries of destination, was attained by Antigua and Barbuda (+91.9% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, the largest markets for steel wire exported from the U.S.  were the UK ($964K), Australia ($508K) and South Korea ($445K), with a combined 27% share of total exports. These countries were followed by the Netherlands, New Zealand, the Dominican Republic, Guatemala, Honduras, Panama, El Salvador, Antigua and Barbuda and Colombia, which together accounted for a further 26%.</p><b>Export Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The averag