es varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest export price was France ($7.2 per unit), while Poland ($2.9 per unit) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of export prices was attained by Luxembourg (+0.8% per year), while the other leaders experienced mixed trends in the export price figures.</p><b style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Shaving Preparations Imports</b><br /><br /><b>Imports in the EU</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, approx. 161M units of pre-shave, shaving and after-shave preparations (excluding soap in blocks) were imported in the European Union; picking up by 7.9% against the previous year. The total imports indicated a strong increase from 2007 to 2017: its volume increased at an average annual rate of +4.1% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. Based on 2017 figures, the shaving preparations imports increased by +84.4% against 2014 indices. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, shaving preparations imports totaled $610M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=330710&region=155\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. The shaving preparations imports continue to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. In that year, shaving preparations imports attained their peak  of $706M. From 2009 to 2017, the growth of shaving preparations imports remained at a somewhat lower figure. </p><b>Imports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>Belgium was the key importer of pre-shave, shaving and after-shave preparations (excluding soap in blocks) in the European Union, with the volume of imports recording 46M units, which was approx. 29% of total imports in 2017. It was distantly followed by Poland (19M units), France (16M units), Italy (15M units), Germany (14M units) and Spain (10M units), together achieving 46% share of total imports. Romania (6.6M units), the Netherlands (6.5M units), the UK (6.3M units) and Slovakia (3.2M units) occupied the weak share of total imports. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Belgium was also the fastest growing in terms of the pre-shave, shaving and after-shave preparations (excluding soap in blocks) imports, with a CAGR of +22.0% from 2007 to 2017. At the same time, Poland (+11.6%), Romania (+9.5%), Slovakia (+8.9%), Italy (+8.6%), Spain (+6.7%) and France (+1.2%) displayed positive paces of growth. Germany and the Netherlands experienced a relatively flat trend pattern. By contrast, the UK (-3.2%) illustrated a downward trend over the same period. While the share of Romania (-2.5%), Spain (-3.1%), Italy (-5.1%), Poland (-8.1%) and Belgium (-24.7%) decreased significantly, the shares of the other countries remained relatively stable throughout the analyzed period. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, the largest shaving preparations markets worldwide were Belgium ($135M), Germany ($89M) and Poland ($59M), with a combined 46% share of total imports. </p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The shaving preparations import price in the European Union stood at $3.8 per unit in 2017, stabilizing at the previous year. The the shaving preparations import price continues to indicate a significant downturn. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Import prices varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest import price was the UK ($9.1 per unit), while France ($1.9 per unit) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by the Netherlands (-0.0% per year), while the other leaders experienced a decline in the import price figures.</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/eu-pre-shave-shaving-and-after-shave-preparations-excluding-soap-in-blocks-market-analysis-forecast-size-trends-and-insights/\" ta