s of the crispbread imports, with a CAGR of +18.8% from 2007 to 2017. At the same time, Belgium (+11.0%), Finland (+8.9%), Spain (+5.5%), Denmark (+3.9%), France (+3.2%), Ireland (+2.6%) and the Netherlands (+1.9%) displayed positive paces of growth. Sweden experienced a relatively flat trend pattern. By contrast, Germany (-1.8%), Italy (-2.4%) and Poland (-2.8%) illustrated a downward trend over the same period. While the share of Italy (1.9%) and Germany (1.8%) increased significantly in terms of the global imports from 2007-2017, the share of Finland (-1.5%), the Netherlands (-1.8%), Belgium (-1.9%), Denmark (-2%), France (-2.7%) and the UK (-19.8%) displayed negative dynamics. The shares of the other countries remained relatively stable throughout the analyzed period. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, the UK ($40M), France ($29M) and the Netherlands ($24M) were the countries with the highest levels of imports in 2017, with a combined 40% share of total imports. </p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The crispbread import price in the European Union stood at $2.7 per kg in 2017, picking up by 2% against the previous year. The the crispbread import price continues to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Import prices varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest import price was Finland ($4.3 per kg), while the UK ($1.9 per kg) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Spain (+3.9% per year), while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/eu-crispbread-market-analysis-forecast-size-trends-and-insights/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 59, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 0),
