major exporting countries. In 2017, major exporting countries recorded the following export prices: in Austria ($1,491 per tonne) and Germany ($1,414 per tonne), while the Netherlands ($1,267 per tonne) and Belgium ($1,355 per tonne) were amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of export prices was attained by Belgium, while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b>Imports in the EU</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, approx. 325K tonnes of melamine were imported in the European Union; rising by 5.9% against the previous year. The melamine imports continue to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, melamine imports amounted to $441M (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=293361&region=155\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. The melamine imports continue to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. Over the period under review, melamine imports attained their maximum at $491M in 2011; however, from 2012 to 2017, imports remained at a lower figure. </p><b>Imports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, Germany (76K tonnes), distantly followed by Belgium (42K tonnes), Italy (36K tonnes), the UK (32K tonnes), Spain (27K tonnes), Romania (20K tonnes), Austria (20K tonnes) and Poland (19K tonnes) were the largest importers of melamine, together comprising 83% of total imports. France (11K tonnes) took the relatively small share of total imports. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of imports, amongst the main importing countries, was attained by Romania, while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, the largest melamine markets worldwide were Germany ($98M), Belgium ($51M) and Italy ($49M), together comprising 45% of total imports. Spain, the UK, Austria, Poland, Romania and France lagged somewhat behind, together accounting for a further 41%.</p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, the melamine import price in the European Union amounted to $1.4 per kg, rising by 7.5% against the previous year. The the melamine import price continues to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. The growth pace was the most rapid in 2008, when the import price increased by 28% y-o-y. The level of import price peaked at $1,782 per tonne in 2011; however, from 2012 to 2017, import prices failed to regain their momentum. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Average import prices varied somewhat amongst the major importing countries. In 2017, major importing countries recorded the following import prices: in France ($1,549 per tonne) and Spain ($1,542 per tonne), while Belgium ($1,220 per tonne) and the UK ($1,251 per tonne) were amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Spain, while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/eu-melamine-market-report-analysis-and-forecast-to-2020/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 101, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 1),
