(105, 'Pesticide Market in Asia 2019 | BASF SE, Bayer AG, DuPont de Nemours Inc., Dow Inc.', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Pesticide Market in Asia 2019 | BASF SE, Bayer AG, DuPont de Nemours Inc., Dow Inc.\" alt=\"Pesticide Market in Asia 2019 | BASF SE, Bayer AG, DuPont de Nemours Inc., Dow Inc.\" height=\"420\" width=\"722\" src=\"https://www.indexbox.io/published/publicdata/U983154/attachments/SC/products_covers_overlays/34620-0.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><p>IndexBox has just published a new report, <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/asia-pesticides-market-analysis-forecast-size-trends-and-insights/\">the Asia - Pesticides - Market Analysis, Forecast, Size, Trends and Insights</a>. Here is a summary of the report\'s key findings.</p><p></p><p>The revenue of the pesticide market in Asia amounted to $27.4B in 2017, increasing by 8.4% against the previous year. This figure reflects the total revenues of producers and importers (excluding logistics costs, retail marketing costs, and retailers\' margins, which will be included in the final consumer price). The total market indicated a remarkable expansion from 2007 to 2017: its value increased at an average annual rate of +6.2% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. The pace of growth appeared the most rapid in 2008, with an increase of 21% y-o-y. Over the period under review, the pesticide market attained its maximum level in 2017, and is likely to see steady growth in the near future. </p><b>Production in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, approx. 7M tonnes of pesticides were produced in Asia; picking up by 8.1% against the previous year. The total output indicated a remarkable expansion from 2007 to 2017: its volume increased at an average annual rate of +7.8% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. Based on 2017 figures, the pesticide production increased by +111.9% against 2007 indices. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p></p><b>Exports in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, the amount of pesticides exported in Asia totaled 2.4M tonnes, growing by 12% against the previous year. Pesticide exports continue to indicate a strong expansion. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, pesticide exports totaled $10.3B (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=3808h1&region=966\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. Pesticide exports continue to indicate a prominent increase. Over the period under review, pesticide exports attained their maximum in 2017, and are expected to retain its growth in the near future. </p><b>Exports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>China represented the largest exporting countries with an export of about 1.6M tonnes, which amounted to 66% of total exports. India (353K tonnes) occupied the second position in the ranking, distantly followed by Israel (121K tonnes). All these countries together occupied approx. 19% share of total exports. Malaysia (90K tonnes), Japan (53K tonnes) and Indonesia (40K tonnes) took the relatively small share of total exports. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Exports from China increased at an average annual rate of +13.3% from 2007 to 2017. At the same time, India (+29.5%), Malaysia (+11.1%), Indonesia (+10.2%) and Israel (+5.1%) displayed positive paces of growth. Moreover, India emerged as the fastest growing exporter in Asia, with a CAGR of +29.5% from 2007-2017. Japan experienced a relatively flat trend pattern. From 2007 to 2017, the share of Israel, Malaysia, India and China decreased by -1.9%, -2.4%, -13.4% and -47.5% percentage points, while the shares of the other countries remained relatively stable throughout the analyzed period. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, China ($4.7B) remains the largest pesticide supplier in Asia, comprising 46% of global exports. The second position in the ranking was occupied by India ($2B), with a 19% share of global exports. It was followed by Israel, with a 13% share.</p><b>Export Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, the pesticide export price in Asia amounted to $4.2 per kg, increasing by 9.9% against the previous year. The pesticide export price continues to indicate a relatively flat trend pattern. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There were significant differences in the average export prices amongst the major exporting countries. In 2017, the country with the highest export price was Israel ($10,837 per tonne), while Malaysia ($2,271 per tonne) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of export prices was attained by Indonesia, while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><b>Imports in Asia</b><br /><br /><p>In 2017, the amount of pesticides imported in Asia stood at 1.1M tonnes, picking up by 10% against the previous year. The total imports indicated a prominent growth from 2007 to 2017: its volume increased at an average annual rate of +7.1% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. Based on 2017 figures, the pesticide imports increased by +99.1% against 2007 indices. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, pesticide imports stood at $6.1B (<a href=\"https://app.indexbox.io/report?product=3808h1&region=966\" target=\"_blank\">IndexBox estimates</a>) in 2017. The total imports indicated a prominent growth from 2007 to 2017: its value increased at an average annual rate of +7.1% over the last decade. The trend pattern, however, indicated some noticeable fluctuations being recorded throughout the analyzed period. Over the period under review, pesticide imports attained their maximum in 2017, and are likely to continue its growth in the immediate term. </p><b>Imports by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The imports of the twelve major importers of pesticides, namely Thailand, Indonesia, India, China, Viet Nam, Japan, the Philippines, Bangladesh, Taiwan, Chinese, Turkey, Malaysia and Kazakhstan, represented more than two-thirds of total import. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of imports, amongst the main importing countries, was attained by Bangladesh, while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In value terms, the largest pesticide markets worldwide were India ($731M), China ($675M) and Thailand ($647M), together comprising 34% of total imports. Viet Nam, Japan, Indonesia, Turkey, Taiwan, Chinese, the Philippines, Bangladesh, Kazakhstan and Malaysia lagged somewhat behind, together accounting for a further 47%.</p><b>Import Prices by Country</b><br /><br /><p>The pesticide import price in Asia stood at $5.4 per kg in 2017, reducing by -2.5% against the previous year. The pesticide import price continues to indicate a mild growth. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Import prices varied noticeably by the country of destination; the country with the highest import price was China ($7,897 per tonne), while Indonesia ($3,362 per tonne) was amongst the lowest.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From 2007 to 2017, the most notable rate of growth in terms of import prices was attained by Viet Nam, while the other leaders experienced more modest paces of growth.</p></p><p>Source: <a href=\"https://www.indexbox.io/store/asia-pesticides-market-analysis-forecast-size-trends-and-insights/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>', 104, '2019-07-18 22:44:15', 0),
